 44	/**
 45	 * The deep module the public routes talk to (CMS plan §"Services", decision
 46	 * D3). `Content` is the single read path for every editable piece of the site:
 47	 * it reads the one bilingual `SiteContent` document from the bucket, decodes it
 48	 * at the boundary (`boundary-discipline`), caches it with a short TTL, and
 49	 * **falls back to the bundled defaults** whenever the bucket is unconfigured,
 50	 * unreachable, or empty (so dev with no bucket behaves exactly like today).
 51	 *
 52	 * Principles (see `~/.brain/principles`):
 53	 *   - `derive-dont-sync`: the current-conference-by-date and by-year selection
 54	 *     logic lives HERE, derived from the one decoded document — it is not
 55	 *     duplicated across routes, and the old `conference.server.ts` /
 56	 *     `team.server.tsx` typed-TS data is deleted, its callers migrated here
 57	 *     (`migrate-callers-then-delete-legacy-apis`, `subtract-before-you-add`).
 58	 *   - `boundary-discipline`: the document crosses the boundary exactly once —
 59	 *     `Schema`-decoded on read — and is converted HERE to the legacy
 60	 *     route/component shape (per-locale strings, `[start, end]` millisecond
 61	 *     tuples, leading-`/` image URLs) so component code is UNCHANGED.
 62	 *   - `use-the-platform`: the read cache is Effect's built-in
 63	 *     `Effect.cachedInvalidateWithTTL` — it single-flights concurrent
 64	 *     first-reads (a fetch in flight parks the other fibers on a latch and they
 65	 *     all get the one result, so the bucket is not stampeded) and hands back an
 66	 *     `invalidate` effect the editor's publish calls (`bust`). Within the TTL it
 67	 *     returns the *same* decoded `SiteContent` reference. **Documented staleness
 68	 *     window:** the built-in `invalidate` is a bare sync that only expires the
 69	 *     entry (`expiresAt = 0`); it does not pre-empt an in-flight refresh nor
 70	 *     clear its `running` flag. So a publish that lands while a refresh is
 71	 *     already fetching the bucket is masked: that refresh's `onExit` completes
 72	 *     with the *pre-publish* document and re-arms the TTL from its own
 73	 *     completion instant. Measured from the publish instant the stale window is
 74	 *     therefore `(the refresh's remaining bucket-read duration) + one TTL` — not
 75	 *     ≤ one TTL. For a 30s-TTL, low-write CMS this worst case (a multi-second
 76	 *     bucket read in flight + 30s) still stays inside D3's "visible on the next
 77	 *     read after the window" contract, so we take the platform primitive over a
 78	 *     hand-rolled epoch guard (`subtract-before-you-add`).
 79	 *   - `make-impossible-states-unrepresentable`: a Conference whose pricing is
 80	 *     undecided carries `registration: undefined` (the `Option.none()` in the
 81	 *     document), never empty tuples.
 82	 *
 83	 * The boundary types below reproduce the shape the routes/components already
 84	 * consume verbatim (`title`, the misnamed-but-rendered `theme` accent colour,
 85	 * `hero.image.{desktop,mobile}`, `hero.alt`, `[start, end]` ms `dates`, optional
 86	 * ms `registration`, `speakers[].img`, …) so migrating the loaders is a
 87	 * one-line swap and the rendered HTML is byte-for-byte the same.
 88	 */
